==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zoisite
<hw>Zois"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[After its
discoverer, Von <ets>Zois</ets>, an Austrian mineralogist.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A grayish or whitish mineral occurring in
orthorhombic, prismatic crystals, also in columnar masses. It is a
silicate of alumina and lime, and is allied to epidote.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zoism</ent>⟦br⟧
